# Trivy ignore list — must include a justification for every line.
# Reviewed: 2026-05-20
#
# Why these CVEs are suppressed:
# Both are Go stdlib CVEs in the Go runtime that was used to compile the
# esbuild binaries shipped inside @esbuild/* and @esbuild-kit/* Node packages.
# Those binaries live under:
#   db-migrate/node_modules/@esbuild/linux-x64/bin/esbuild
#   db-migrate/node_modules/@esbuild-kit/core-utils/node_modules/esbuild/bin/esbuild
#
# They run at BUILD time only (TypeScript transpilation, bundling). In the
# runtime image they are never executed:
#   - The Next.js standalone runtime at /app uses the build's output, not esbuild
#   - The drizzle-kit migrate runner at /app/db-migrate calls `drizzle-kit
#     migrate` which uses esbuild to parse drizzle.config.ts ONCE per deploy,
#     and the resulting process never accepts network traffic (no HTTP, no TLS)
#
# The vulnerabilities:
#   CVE-2024-24790 — net/netip IPv4-mapped IPv6 misbehaviour. esbuild does
#                    not use net/netip in any code path we invoke.
#   CVE-2025-68121 — crypto/tls cert validation during TLS resumption.
#                    esbuild does not perform TLS in our invocation.
#
# Action items if anything changes:
#   - If drizzle-kit gains a feature that opens network connections, remove
#     this ignore and either prune the esbuild binaries (need to switch
#     drizzle.config.ts → .mjs first) or pin a fixed Go-runtime esbuild.
#   - Re-review on next esbuild major version bump.
CVE-2024-24790
CVE-2025-68121
